Enhance the cybersecurity at your home

In this activity, I made several improvements to enhance cybersecurity in my living environment.

1. I enabled Face ID on my phone to ensure that only I can access my device. This improves security by using biometric authentication instead of relying only on a password.

2. I also used a VPN when connecting to public Wi-Fi networks. This helps encrypt my internet traffic and reduces the risk of data being intercepted.

3. I made sure that my important accounts use two-factor authentication where possible. This adds an extra layer of security and reduces the risk of unauthorised access.

4. I ensured that my devices are updated regularly. Keeping software up to date helps fix security vulnerabilities and protect against known threats.

Overall, these changes improved my personal cybersecurity by strengthening authentication, protecting accounts, and reducing risks from common attacks.
